---

## testsmells.org 19-Smell Catalog Audit

**Project:** `DataAccess.IntegrationTests` · **Framework:** MSTest v4 · **Scope:** `UserRepositoryIntegrationTests.cs` (8 tests)

### Summary Dashboard

| Severity | Smells Found | Affected Tests |
|----------|-------------|----------------|
| **High** | 3 | 3 |
| **Medium** | 1 | 1 |
| Low | 0 | 0 |
| **Total** | **4** | **4 unique** |

**13 of 19 catalog smells were not detected.** The remaining 4 tests (50%) are clean.

---

### HIGH Findings

#### 1. Sleepy Test — `NotifyOnInsert_SendsEventAfterDelay` (line 87)

```csharp
Thread.Sleep(3000);  // ← hardcoded 3-second wait
```

**Why it's a problem:** Even in integration tests, `Thread.Sleep` is a smell (Camara et al., SAST 2021 links Sleepy Test to flakiness). On a slow CI agent the 3 s may not be enough; on every run it wastes 3 s whether the event fires in 50 ms or not.

**Fix — poll with a timeout:**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
public async Task NotifyOnInsert_SendsEventAfterDelay()
{
    var user = new User("dave@example.com", "Dave");
    _repository.Insert(user);

    // Poll with back-off instead of sleeping a fixed duration
    var deadline = DateTime.UtcNow.AddSeconds(5);
    while (DateTime.UtcNow < deadline)
    {
        if (_repository.WasNotificationSent(user.Id))
            break;
        await Task.Delay(100);
    }

    Assert.IsTrue(_repository.WasNotificationSent(user.Id),
        "Notification was not sent within the timeout window.");
}
```

---

#### 2. Conditional Test Logic — `GetUser_ReturnsCorrectType` (lines 101-108)

```csharp
if (loaded is PremiumUser premium)
{
    Assert.IsTrue(premium.DiscountRate > 0);
}
else
{
    Assert.AreEqual("Eve", loaded!.Name);
}
```

**Why it's a problem:** One branch is never exercised per run, so half the "test" is dead code. If `PremiumUser` logic breaks, the `else` branch silently passes.

**Fix — split into two deterministic tests:**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void GetUser_StandardUser_ReturnsName()
{
    _repository.Insert(new User("eve@example.com", "Eve"));
    var loaded = _repository.GetByEmail("eve@example.com");

    Assert.IsNotNull(loaded);
    Assert.AreEqual("Eve", loaded.Name);
}

[TestMethod]
public void GetUser_PremiumUser_HasPositiveDiscount()
{
    _repository.InsertPremium(new PremiumUser("vip@example.com", "VIP", discountRate: 0.1m));
    var loaded = (PremiumUser)_repository.GetByEmail("vip@example.com")!;

    Assert.IsTrue(loaded.DiscountRate > 0, "Premium user should have a positive discount.");
}
```

---

#### 3. Assertion-Free Test (a.k.a. Unknown Test) — `BulkInsert_RunsWithoutErrors` (lines 112-119)

```csharp
public void BulkInsert_RunsWithoutErrors()
{
    for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++)
        _repository.Insert(new User($"bulk{i}@example.com", $"Bulk User {i}"));
    // ← no assertion — passes even if Insert silently drops every row
}
```

**Why it's a problem:** MSTest marks this green as long as no exception is thrown. If `Insert` is a no-op, the test still passes — pure false confidence.

**Fix — assert an observable outcome:**
```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void BulkInsert_PersistsAllRecords()
{
    for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++)
        _repository.Insert(new User($"bulk{i}@example.com", $"Bulk User {i}"));

    var users = _repository.ListAll();
    Assert.AreEqual(100, users.Count, "All 100 bulk-inserted users should be persisted.");
}
```

---

### MEDIUM Finding

#### 4. Assertion Roulette — `InsertUser_PersistsToDatabase` (lines 35-38)

```csharp
Assert.IsNotNull(loaded);
Assert.AreEqual("Alice", loaded.Name);
Assert.AreEqual("alice@example.com", loaded.Email);
Assert.IsTrue(loaded.Id > 0);
// 4 assertions, 0 messages — which one failed?
```

**Why it's a problem (Peruma et al., ESEC/FSE 2020):** With 4 bare assertions a CI failure produces only `Assert.AreEqual failed. Expected:<Alice>. Actual:<null>.` — no business context.

**Fix — add descriptive messages:**
```csharp
Assert.IsNotNull(loaded, "User should be retrievable after insert.");
Assert.AreEqual("Alice", loaded.Name, "Persisted name should match.");
Assert.AreEqual("alice@example.com", loaded.Email, "Persisted email should match.");
Assert.IsTrue(loaded.Id > 0, "Database should assign a positive ID.");
```

---

### Smells Not Detected (15 of 19) ✓

| # | Smell | Status |
|---|-------|--------|
| 2 | Mystery Guest | ✅ Clean — in-memory SQLite, no external resources |
| 5 | Eager Test | ✅ Clean — multi-method calls are appropriate for integration scope |
| 6 | Magic Number Test | ✅ Clean — `3` and `10` are self-documenting (items just added) |
| 7 | Sensitive Equality | ✅ No `ToString()` in assertions |
| 8 | Exception Handling | ✅ No try/catch in tests |
| 9 | General Fixture | ✅ `_connection`/`_repository` used by every test |
| 10 | Ignored Test | ✅ No skipped tests |
| 11 | Duplicate Assert | ✅ No repeated assertions |
| 12 | Lazy Test | ✅ Each test targets a distinct behavior |
| 13 | Constructor Initialization | ✅ Uses `[TestInitialize]` correctly |
| 14 | Default Test | ✅ Class is properly named |
| 15 | Redundant Print | ✅ No debug output |
| 16 | Redundant Assertion | ✅ No tautological assertions |
| 17 | Resource Optimism | ✅ In-memory DB, no file-system assumptions |
| 18 | Empty Test | ✅ No empty methods |

### What This Suite Does Well

- **Proper lifecycle management** — `[TestInitialize]`/`[TestCleanup]` with disposal; each test gets a fresh in-memory DB (excellent isolation).
- **`sealed` test class** — prevents fragile inheritance hierarchies.
- **Clear AAA structure** in `InsertUser`, `UpdateUser`, `DeleteUser`, and `ListUsers`.
- **Appropriate integration scope** — tests exercise real SQLite, not over-mocked fakes.
- **Concurrency test** (`ConcurrentInserts`) is a strong addition most suites lack.

### Prioritized Remediation

| Priority | Smell | Fix effort | Impact |
|----------|-------|-----------|--------|
| 1 | **Assertion-Free Test** | ~2 min | Eliminates false confidence |
| 2 | **Conditional Test Logic** | ~5 min | Guarantees both branches are tested |
| 3 | **Sleepy Test** | ~5 min | Removes flakiness + speeds CI by ≤3 s |
| 4 | **Assertion Roulette** | ~3 min | Improves failure diagnostics |

**Bottom line:** 4 of 8 tests are clean and well-designed. The other 4 each carry exactly one smell — no test has compounding issues. Fixes 1-3 (≈12 min) would eliminate all High-severity findings.
